10. packages/gov-client/README.md

# @ardtire/gov-client

Typed TypeScript client for the Ardtire Society Governance API.

## Purpose

`@ardtire/gov-client` is the canonical consumer SDK for `apps/gov-api`.

It provides:

- typed request and response contracts
- module-oriented domain client methods
- centralized auth header injection
- normalized Problem Details error handling
- mockable client interfaces for application tests

## Design principles

- read DTOs and write DTOs remain distinct
- governance lifecycle commands are exposed as explicit methods
- API error responses are normalized into `GovApiError`
- HTTP transport details are hidden behind domain-oriented modules

## Example

```ts
import { createGovClient } from "@ardtire/gov-client";

const govClient = createGovClient({
  baseUrl: "http://localhost:3002/api/v1",
  getAccessToken: async () => process.env.ACCESS_TOKEN ?? null,
});

const proposal = await govClient.proposals.createDraft({
  title: "Founding Resolution",
  bodyMarkdown: "# Founding Resolution\n\nText...",
});

Error handling

import { GovApiError, isGovApiError } from "@ardtire/gov-client";

try {
  await govClient.ballots.open(ballotId);
} catch (error) {
  if (isGovApiError(error)) {
    console.error(error.status, error.problem.code, error.problem.detail);
  }
  throw error;
}

Available modules

identity

membership

governance

roles

proposals

ballots

certifications

records

gazette

